  "purpose": "Validate a local read-only Mira Core readiness/index manifest over Phases 1-12. The manifest answers what exists, what is real now, what remains proposal or validation only, what capabilities are allowed, what is blocked, what proof is missing or degraded, and what Tier 0/Tier 1 next actions are safe without executing any work.",
  "nonGoals": [
    "No runtime implementation in this Oracle fixture.",
    "No source-store writes from the readiness manifest.",
    "No memory or profile commits.",
    "No network requests.",
    "No server deployment or server process.",
    "No queue creation.",
    "No database writes.",
    "No auth, secret, or signing material generation.",
    "No local execution.",
    "No shell or PTY actions.",
    "No browser, screenshot, OCR, or window access.",
    "No external sends or customer sends.",
    "No deploys.",
    "No trades or financial actions.",
    "No claim that a manifest, socket, lease, route, or upload envelope proves model processing."
  ],
  "builderPatchMustSatisfy": {
    "scope": [
      "Build a local read-only readiness_manifest and validation_report over the existing Mira Core Phase 1-12 artifact surface.",
      "Represent all twelve prior phases with phase number, module path, CLI path, test path, fixture path, status, boundary mode, real-now summary, and evidence refs.",
      "Index schemas and CLI entry points without claiming that stdout JSON or local validators create server, queue, capture, apply, memory commit, or execution capability.",
      "Preserve local/server capability truth, including serverCanExecuteLocal=false and serverCanProveModelProcessing=false.",
      "Report verification proof honestly: only commands/results actually supplied or observed may be marked proven; missing proof is unknown or degraded.",
      "Expose blockers for real server runtime, durable mutation, capture/apply/execution, and memory drift.",
      "Emit only Tier 0/Tier 1 next recommendations with why-safe text and evidence refs.",
      "Emit side_effect_result showing no runtime writes, network, server, queue, db, execution, shell, browser, sends, deploys, trades, or output-file write performed by manifest generation."
    ],
    "hardRejects": [
      "Manifest labels a contract-only, proposal-only, dry-run, upload-envelope, intent-record, mutation-patch, perception-proposal, or server-boundary phase as live server/runtime/capture/apply/execution behavior.",
      "Manifest claims a future server can run local arms, operate PTY, run shell, access browser/window state, send customer messages, deploy, trade, or prove model processing.",
      "Manifest allows direct server targeting of Builder or Oracle instead of local Architect.",
      "Manifest treats socket connection, queue acceptance, dry-run lease, route delivery, or manifest generation as bridge-green or model-processing proof.",
      "Manifest includes raw private content, secrets, raw comms, raw terminal scrollback, screenshot/OCR text, browser state, customer private content, side-profile content, or raw source-store payloads.",
      "Manifest fakes test proof, omits unknown/degraded proof, or promotes missing command results to green status.",
      "Manifest omits blockers for server identity/signing/auth/storage/deletion/retention, memory/profile commits, capture/apply/execution local gates, or memory drift.",
      "Manifest recommends Tier 2 repo mutation, Tier 3 external side effects, Tier 4 financial/irreversible actions, server deploys, customer sends, trades, real queues, durable commits, or capture/apply/execution as next safe actions."
    ]
  },
